physical_examinations.vital_signs: Tachypnea and tachycardia observed at 6 days of age
physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Severe heart failure with prominent trabeculation of the left ventricle and blood signals within the intertrabecular region. Continued pericardial effusion, pleural effusion, and ascites for 77 days.
